play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Than but to know't a little.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: How now, my lord!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: What sense had I of her stol'n hours of lust?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I saw't not, thought it not, it harm'd not me:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I slept the next night well, was free and merry;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I found not Cassio's kisses on her lips:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: He that is robb'd, not wanting what is stol'n,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Let him not know't, and he's not robb'd at all.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I am sorry to hear this.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I had been happy, if the general camp,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Pioners and all, had tasted her sweet body,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: So I had nothing known. O, now, for ever
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Farewell the tranquil mind! farewell content!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Farewell the plumed troop, and the big wars,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That make ambition virtue! O, farewell!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Farewell the neighing steed, and the shrill trump,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: The spirit-stirring drum, the ear-piercing fife,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: The royal banner, and all quality,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Pride, pomp and circumstance of glorious war!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And, O you mortal engines, whose rude throats
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: The immortal Jove's dead clamours counterfeit,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Farewell! Othello's occupation's gone!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Is't possible, my lord?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Villain, be sure thou prove my love a whore,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Be sure of it; give me the ocular proof:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Or by the worth of man's eternal soul,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Thou hadst been better have been born a dog
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Than answer my waked wrath!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Is't come to this?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Make me to see't; or, at the least, so prove it,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That the probation bear no hinge nor loop
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To hang a doubt on; or woe upon thy life!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: My noble lord,--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: If thou dost slander her and torture me,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Never pray more; abandon all remorse;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: On horror's head horrors accumulate;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Do deeds to make heaven weep, all earth amazed;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: For nothing canst thou to damnation add
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Greater than that.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: O grace! O heaven forgive me!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Are you a man? have you a soul or sense?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: God be wi' you; take mine office. O wretched fool.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That livest to make thine honesty a vice!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: O monstrous world! Take note, take note, O world,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To be direct and honest is not safe.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I thank you for this profit; and from hence
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I'll love no friend, sith love breeds such offence.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Nay, stay: thou shouldst be honest.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I should be wise, for honesty's a fool
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And loses that it works for.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: By the world,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I think my wife be honest and think she is not;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I think that thou art just and think thou art not.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I'll have some proof. Her name, that was as fresh
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: As Dian's visage, is now begrimed and black
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: As mine own face. If there be cords, or knives,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Poison, or fire, or suffocating streams,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I'll not endure it. Would I were satisfied!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I see, sir, you are eaten up with passion:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I do repent me that I put it to you.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: You would be satisfied?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Would! nay, I will.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And may: but, how? how satisfied, my lord?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Would you, the supervisor, grossly gape on--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Behold her topp'd?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Death and damnation! O!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: It were a tedious difficulty, I think,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To bring them to that prospect: damn them then,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: If ever mortal eyes do see them bolster
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: More than their own! What then? how then?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: What shall I say? Where's satisfaction?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: It is impossible you should see this,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Were they as prime as goats, as hot as monkeys,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: As salt as wolves in pride, and fools as gross
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: As ignorance made drunk. But yet, I say,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: If imputation and strong circumstances,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Which lead directly to the door of truth,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Will give you satisfaction, you may have't.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Give me a living reason she's disloyal.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I do not like the office:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: But, sith I am enter'd in this cause so far,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Prick'd to't by foolish honesty and love,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I will go on. I lay with Cassio lately;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And, being troubled with a raging tooth,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I could not sleep.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: There are a kind of men so loose of soul,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That in their sleeps will mutter their affairs:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: One of this kind is Cassio:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: In sleep I heard him say 'Sweet Desdemona,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Let us be wary, let us hide our loves;'
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And then, sir, would he gripe and wring my hand,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Cry 'O sweet creature!' and then kiss me hard,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: As if he pluck'd up kisses by the roots
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That grew upon my lips: then laid his leg
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Over my thigh, and sigh'd, and kiss'd; and then
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Cried 'Cursed fate that gave thee to the Moor!'
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: O monstrous! monstrous!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Nay, this was but his dream.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: But this denoted a foregone conclusion:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: 'Tis a shrewd doubt, though it be but a dream.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And this may help to thicken other proofs
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That do demonstrate thinly.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I'll tear her all to pieces.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Nay, but be wise: yet we see nothing done;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: She may be honest yet. Tell me but this,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Have you not sometimes seen a handkerchief
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Spotted with strawberries in your wife's hand?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I gave her such a one; 'twas my first gift.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I know not that; but such a handkerchief--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I am sure it was your wife's--did I to-day
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: See Cassio wipe his beard with.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: If it be that--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: If it be that, or any that was hers,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: It speaks against her with the other proofs.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: O, that the slave had forty thousand lives!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: One is too poor, too weak for my revenge.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Now do I see 'tis true. Look here, Iago;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: All my fond love thus do I blow to heaven.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: 'Tis gone.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Arise, black vengeance, from thy hollow cell!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Yield up, O love, thy crown and hearted throne
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To tyrannous hate! Swell, bosom, with thy fraught,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: For 'tis of aspics' tongues!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Yet be content.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: O, blood, blood, blood!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Patience, I say; your mind perhaps may change.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Never, Iago: Like to the Pontic sea,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Whose icy current and compulsive course
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Ne'er feels retiring ebb, but keeps due on
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To the Propontic and the Hellespont,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Even so my bloody thoughts, with violent pace,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Shall ne'er look back, ne'er ebb to humble love,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Till that a capable and wide revenge
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Swallow them up. Now, by yond marble heaven,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: In the due reverence of a sacred vow
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I here engage my words.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Do not rise yet.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Witness, you ever-burning lights above,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: You elements that clip us round about,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Witness that here Iago doth give up
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: The execution of his wit, hands, heart,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To wrong'd Othello's service! Let him command,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And to obey shall be in me remorse,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: What bloody business ever.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I greet thy love,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Not with vain thanks, but with acceptance bounteous,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: And will upon the instant put thee to't:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Within these three days let me hear thee say
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: That Cassio's not alive.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: My friend is dead; 'tis done at your request:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: But let her live.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Damn her, lewd minx! O, damn her!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Come, go with me apart; I will withdraw,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: To furnish me with some swift means of death
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: For the fair devil. Now art thou my lieutenant.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: I am your own for ever.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE III.  The garden of the castle.

line_text: Do you know, sirrah, where Lieutenant Cassio lies?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I dare not say he lies any where.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Why, man?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: He's a soldier, and for one to say a soldier lies,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: is stabbing.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Go to: where lodges he?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To tell you where he lodges, is to tell you where I lie.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Can any thing be made of this?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I know not where he lodges, and for me to devise a
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: lodging and say he lies here or he lies there, were
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: to lie in mine own throat.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Can you inquire him out, and be edified by report?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I will catechise the world for him; that is, make
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: questions, and by them answer.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Seek him, bid him come hither: tell him I have
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: moved my lord on his behalf, and hope all will be well.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To do this is within the compass of man's wit: and
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: therefore I will attempt the doing it.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Where should I lose that handkerchief, Emilia?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I know not, madam.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Believe me, I had rather have lost my purse
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Full of crusadoes: and, but my noble Moor
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is true of mind and made of no such baseness
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: As jealous creatures are, it were enough
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To put him to ill thinking.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is he not jealous?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Who, he? I think the sun where he was born
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Drew all such humours from him.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Look, where he comes.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I will not leave him now till Cassio
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Be call'd to him.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: How is't with you, my lord
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Well, my good lady.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: O, hardness to dissemble!--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: How do you, Desdemona?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Well, my good lord.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Give me your hand: this hand is moist, my lady.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: It yet hath felt no age nor known no sorrow.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: This argues fruitfulness and liberal heart:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Hot, hot, and moist: this hand of yours requires
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: A sequester from liberty, fasting and prayer,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Much castigation, exercise devout;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: For here's a young and sweating devil here,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That commonly rebels. 'Tis a good hand,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: A frank one.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: You may, indeed, say so;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: For 'twas that hand that gave away my heart.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: A liberal hand: the hearts of old gave hands;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But our new heraldry is hands, not hearts.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I cannot speak of this. Come now, your promise.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: What promise, chuck?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I have sent to bid Cassio come speak with you.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I have a salt and sorry rheum offends me;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Lend me thy handkerchief.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Here, my lord.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That which I gave you.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I have it not about me.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Not?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: No, indeed, my lord.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That is a fault.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That handkerchief
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Did an Egyptian to my mother give;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: She was a charmer, and could almost read
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: The thoughts of people: she told her, while
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: she kept it,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: 'Twould make her amiable and subdue my father
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Entirely to her love, but if she lost it
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Or made gift of it, my father's eye
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Should hold her loathed and his spirits should hunt
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: After new fancies: she, dying, gave it me;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And bid me, when my fate would have me wive,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To give it her. I did so: and take heed on't;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Make it a darling like your precious eye;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To lose't or give't away were such perdition
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: As nothing else could match.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is't possible?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: 'Tis true: there's magic in the web of it:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: A sibyl, that had number'd in the world
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: The sun to course two hundred compasses,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: In her prophetic fury sew'd the work;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: The worms were hallow'd that did breed the silk;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And it was dyed in mummy which the skilful
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Conserved of maidens' hearts.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Indeed! is't true?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Most veritable; therefore look to't well.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Then would to God that I had never seen't!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Ha! wherefore?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Why do you speak so startingly and rash?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is't lost? is't gone? speak, is it out
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: o' the way?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Heaven bless us!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Say you?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: It is not lost; but what an if it were?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: How!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I say, it is not lost.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Fetch't, let me see't.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Why, so I can, sir, but I will not now.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: This is a trick to put me from my suit:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Pray you, let Cassio be received again.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Fetch me the handkerchief: my mind misgives.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Come, come;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: You'll never meet a more sufficient man.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: The handkerchief!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I pray, talk me of Cassio.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: The handkerchief!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: A man that all his time
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Hath founded his good fortunes on your love,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Shared dangers with you,--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: The handkerchief!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: In sooth, you are to blame.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Away!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is not this man jealous?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I ne'er saw this before.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Sure, there's some wonder in this handkerchief:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I am most unhappy in the loss of it.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: 'Tis not a year or two shows us a man:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: They are all but stomachs, and we all but food;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To eat us hungerly, and when they are full,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: They belch us. Look you, Cassio and my husband!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: There is no other way; 'tis she must do't:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And, lo, the happiness! go, and importune her.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: How now, good Cassio! what's the news with you?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Madam, my former suit: I do beseech you
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That by your virtuous means I may again
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Exist, and be a member of his love
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Whom I with all the office of my heart
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Entirely honour: I would not be delay'd.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: If my offence be of such mortal kind
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That nor my service past, nor present sorrows,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Nor purposed merit in futurity,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Can ransom me into his love again,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But to know so must be my benefit;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: So shall I clothe me in a forced content,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And shut myself up in some other course,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To fortune's alms.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Alas, thrice-gentle Cassio!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: My advocation is not now in tune;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: My lord is not my lord; nor should I know him,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Were he in favour as in humour alter'd.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: So help me every spirit sanctified,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: As I have spoken for you all my best
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And stood within the blank of his displeasure
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: For my free speech! you must awhile be patient:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: What I can do I will; and more I will
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Than for myself I dare: let that suffice you.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is my lord angry?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: He went hence but now,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And certainly in strange unquietness.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Can he be angry? I have seen the cannon,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: When it hath blown his ranks into the air,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And, like the devil, from his very arm
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Puff'd his own brother:--and can he be angry?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: There's matter in't indeed, if he be angry.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I prithee, do so.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Something, sure, of state,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Either from Venice, or some unhatch'd practise
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Made demonstrable here in Cyprus to him,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Hath puddled his clear spirit: and in such cases
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Men's natures wrangle with inferior things,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Though great ones are their object. 'Tis even so;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: For let our finger ache, and it indues
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Our other healthful members even to that sense
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Of pain: nay, we must think men are not gods,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Nor of them look for such observances
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: As fit the bridal. Beshrew me much, Emilia,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I was, unhandsome warrior as I am,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Arraigning his unkindness with my soul;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But now I find I had suborn'd the witness,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And he's indicted falsely.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Pray heaven it be state-matters, as you think,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And no conception nor no jealous toy
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Concerning you.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Alas the day! I never gave him cause.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But jealous souls will not be answer'd so;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: They are not ever jealous for the cause,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But jealous for they are jealous: 'tis a monster
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Begot upon itself, born on itself.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Heaven keep that monster from Othello's mind!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Lady, amen.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I will go seek him. Cassio, walk hereabout:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: If I do find him fit, I'll move your suit
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And seek to effect it to my uttermost.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I humbly thank your ladyship.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Save you, friend Cassio!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: What make you from home?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: How is it with you, my most fair Bianca?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I' faith, sweet love, I was coming to your house.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And I was going to your lodging, Cassio.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: What, keep a week away? seven days and nights?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Eight score eight hours? and lovers' absent hours,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: More tedious than the dial eight score times?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: O weary reckoning!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Pardon me, Bianca:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I have this while with leaden thoughts been press'd:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But I shall, in a more continuate time,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Strike off this score of absence. Sweet Bianca,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Take me this work out.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: O Cassio, whence came this?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: This is some token from a newer friend:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To the felt absence now I feel a cause:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Is't come to this? Well, well.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Go to, woman!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Throw your vile guesses in the devil's teeth,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: From whence you have them. You are jealous now
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: That this is from some mistress, some remembrance:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: No, in good troth, Bianca.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Why, whose is it?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I know not, sweet: I found it in my chamber.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I like the work well: ere it be demanded--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: As like enough it will--I'ld have it copied:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Take it, and do't; and leave me for this time.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Leave you! wherefore?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I do attend here on the general;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And think it no addition, nor my wish,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: To have him see me woman'd.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Why, I pray you?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Not that I love you not.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: But that you do not love me.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: I pray you, bring me on the way a little,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: And say if I shall see you soon at night.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: 'Tis but a little way that I can bring you;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: For I attend here: but I'll see you soon.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: 'Tis very good; I must be circumstanced.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.

line_text: Will you think so?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Think so, Iago!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: What,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: To kiss in private?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: An unauthorized kiss.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Or to be naked with her friend in bed
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: An hour or more, not meaning any harm?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Naked in bed, Iago, and not mean harm!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: It is hypocrisy against the devil:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: They that mean virtuously, and yet do so,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: The devil their virtue tempts, and they tempt heaven.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: So they do nothing, 'tis a venial slip:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: But if I give my wife a handkerchief,--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: What then?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Why, then, 'tis hers, my lord; and, being hers,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: She may, I think, bestow't on any man.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: She is protectress of her honour too:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: May she give that?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Her honour is an essence that's not seen;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: They have it very oft that have it not:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: But, for the handkerchief,--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: By heaven, I would most gladly have forgot it.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Thou said'st, it comes o'er my memory,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: As doth the raven o'er the infected house,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Boding to all--he had my handkerchief.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Ay, what of that?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: That's not so good now.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: What,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: If I had said I had seen him do you wrong?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Or heard him say,--as knaves be such abroad,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Who having, by their own importunate suit,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Or voluntary dotage of some mistress,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Convinced or supplied them, cannot choose
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: But they must blab--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Hath he said any thing?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: He hath, my lord; but be you well assured,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: No more than he'll unswear.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: What hath he said?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: 'Faith, that he did--I know not what he did.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: What? what?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Lie--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: With her?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: With her, on her; what you will.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Lie with her! lie on her! We say lie on her, when
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: they belie her. Lie with her! that's fulsome.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: --Handkerchief--confessions--handkerchief!--To
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: confess, and be hanged for his labour;--first, to be
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: hanged, and then to confess.--I tremble at it.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Nature would not invest herself in such shadowing
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: passion without some instruction. It is not words
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: that shake me thus. Pish! Noses, ears, and lips.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: --Is't possible?--Confess--handkerchief!--O devil!--
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Work on,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: My medicine, work! Thus credulous fools are caught;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: And many worthy and chaste dames even thus,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: All guiltless, meet reproach. What, ho! my lord!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: My lord, I say! Othello!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: How now, Cassio!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: What's the matter?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: My lord is fall'n into an epilepsy:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: This is his second fit; he had one yesterday.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Rub him about the temples.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: No, forbear;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: The lethargy must have his quiet course:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: If not, he foams at mouth and by and by
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Breaks out to savage madness. Look he stirs:
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Do you withdraw yourself a little while,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: He will recover straight: when he is gone,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: I would on great occasion speak with you.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: How is it, general? have you not hurt your head?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Dost thou mock me?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: I mock you! no, by heaven.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Would you would bear your fortune like a man!
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: A horned man's a monster and a beast.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: There's many a beast then in a populous city,
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: And many a civil monster.
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Did he confess it?
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Good sir, be a man;
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: Think every bearded fellow that's but yoked
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: May draw with you: there's millions now alive
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
scene_title: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

line_text: That nightly lie in those unproper beds
play_title_long: The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice
